<task id="UDSS-001" project="UI Dialog Shell Standardization">
  <metadata>
    <title>Define IDataService, IUploadService, INavigationService interfaces</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>shared-library, types, architecture</tags>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>P1-foundation</parallel-group>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Define the core service abstraction interfaces that decouple wizard components from their runtime environment. These interfaces enable wizards to run in both PCF (inline) and Code Page (navigateTo) contexts by abstracting Xrm.WebApi, file upload, and navigation operations behind portable contracts.</prompt>
  <role>Senior TypeScript architect</role>
  <goal>Service abstraction interfaces defined and exported from @spaarke/ui-components/types</goal>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Service portability tiers — shared components MUST NOT reference Xrm.WebApi directly; use IDataService abstraction instead</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/SHARED-UI-COMPONENTS-GUIDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read existing types in src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/types/ to understand current type exports and conventions</step>
    <step id="2">Create serviceInterfaces.ts with IDataService (createRecord, retrieveRecord, retrieveMultipleRecords, updateRecord, deleteRecord), IUploadService (uploadFile, getContainerIdForEntity), INavigationService (openRecord, openDialog, closeDialog)</step>
    <step id="3">Export from types/index.ts barrel</step>
    <step id="4">Run tsc to verify compilation and type correctness</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>All three interfaces (IDataService, IUploadService, INavigationService) compile without errors</criterion>
    <criterion>Interfaces are exported from the types barrel (types/index.ts)</criterion>
    <criterion>No Xrm references exist in the interface definitions</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
